# Compose Multiplatform skeleton — project rules

## Purpose
Reusable **Kotlin Multiplatform** app (Android + iOS) with **Compose Multiplatform**. Prefer clear layers and config over one-off hacks. This file adapts “Android skeleton” ideas to **this** codebase (not Fragment Navigation).

## Core rules
- Write code that is easy to extend and copy into new apps.
- Prefer clarity over micro-optimizations.
- Document non-trivial types and functions with a short KDoc (especially repositories, use cases, and networking).
- Use **use cases** (`domain/usecase/`) for multi-step or heavy domain work; name by intent (e.g. `GenerateCycleUseCase`).

## Naming & style
- **Repository interfaces:** `XxxRepository` in `domain/repository/`. **Implementations:** `XxxRepositoryImpl` in `data/repository/impl/`.
- **HTTP facades:** `XxxApi` in `data/remote/api/` (see `PostApi`, `ApiPath`). **DTOs:** `*Dto` in `data/remote/dto/` (group in subpackages if many).
- Shared **extensions/utilities:** prefer `common/` (e.g. `common/Resource.kt`). UI-only helpers stay under `ui/`.
- **Lambdas:** prefer explicit parameter names when it aids readability (e.g. `defaultValue = { index -> … }`).
- **MutableStateFlow / UI state:** prefer `_uiState.value = _uiState.value.copy(...)` over `update { }` for state writes in ViewModels (consistent, easy to debug).

## Tech stack (this repo)
- **Language:** Kotlin (common + platform source sets)
- **UI:** Compose Multiplatform + Material3
- **DI:** Koin (`injection/*Module.kt`)
- **Navigation:** Type-safe Compose destinations (`navigation/ComposeDestination.kt`, `ComposeNavGraph.kt`)
- **Network:** Ktor Client (`network/`, `data/remote/api/`)
- **Local:** Room, DataStore
- **Config:** `core/config/AppConfig.kt` (API base URL, HTTP timeouts); `common/Constant.kt` (app constants)

## Package layout (KMP)
- **domain/** — `model/`, `repository/` (interfaces), `usecase/`. No Ktor/Room types.
- **data/** — `remote/api/` (`ApiPath`, `*Api`), `remote/dto/`, `remote/mapper/`, `remote/util/` (`safeApiCall`, `safeApiCallFlow`), `repository/impl/`, `database/`, `datastore/`.
- **core/** — `config/` (`AppConfig`), shared non-UI infrastructure.
- **common/** — `Resource`, `Constant`, shared types.
- **network/** — Ktor engine expect/actual, `HttpClientFactory`.
- **ui/** — screens, ViewModels, components, theme.
- **injection/** — Koin modules (`appModule()` composes network, datastore, database, repository, viewModel).

## API & data
- Put relative paths in **`data/remote/api/ApiPath.kt`**; base URL in **`AppConfig.apiBaseUrl`**.
- New resource: add `*Api` + DTOs + mapper + **`domain.repository.XxxRepository`** + **`XxxRepositoryImpl`**; register in `ModuleNetwork` / `ModuleRepository`.
- Wrap remote calls with **`safeApiCall`** / **`safeApiCallFlow`**; expose **`Resource<T>`** (`Loading` / `Success` / `Error`). Map errors to UI strings in ViewModels or small UI mappers (no `Context` in `commonMain` — use platform `actual` if you need localized system messages).
